\fs40 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb3 What makes SolidJS different from other JavaScript frameworks, and is it worth your time as a developer in 2025?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 As a software engineer myself, this framework caught my eye, not only because it looks like React, but rather for its fast performance. I love writing code, especially with React, but SolidJS offers something special that deserves attention.\cb1 \
\cb3 SolidJS has been gaining significant traction in the frontend development world. As developers seek alternatives to React and other established frameworks, Solid offers a compelling mix of performance and developer experience.\cb1 \
\cb3 Now let\'92s just dig deeper into how SolidJS is a very good and a solid choice for a frontend apps.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs60 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb3 The Performance Advantage\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs40 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb3 First and foremost let\'92s talk about the performance advantage that SolidJS gives you as a Developer.\cb1 \
\cb3 SolidJS consistently ranks at the top of JavaScript framework benchmarks, often outperforming React, Vue, and Angular by significant margins. This isn\'92t just marketing \'97 it\'92s measurable in real-world applications.\cb1 \
\cb3 The key to Solid\'92s speed lies in its compilation approach. Unlike React, which uses a virtual DOM and constant re-rendering, SolidJS compiles your components into efficient DOM operations that run once and then update only what\'92s needed.\cb1 \
\cb3 This architectural difference means that Solid applications typically run 5\'9610x faster than equivalent React applications, with smoother rendering and less jank during complex UI updates.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
