\f2\b\fs60 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb3 Fine-Grained Reactivity\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs40 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb3 Reactive by design\cb1 \
\cb3 Solid\'92s reactivity system is built on fine-grained reactivity principles, similar to Vue\'92s Composition API but with even less overhead. Your UI updates automatically when data changes, without unnecessary re-renders.\cb1 \
\cb3 This approach eliminates the need for complex optimization strategies like memoization, useMemo, or shouldComponentUpdate that React developers often struggle with.\cb1 \
\cb3 In practice, this means your application logic becomes more straightforward. When a piece of state changes, only the DOM nodes that depend on that state update, not entire component trees.\cb1 \
\cb3 So you can basically say that SolidJS is a super fast JavaScript framework that updates only what\'92s needed, making it perfect for building apps with great detail and control.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs60 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb3 Developer Experience\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs40 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb3 Let\'92s now talk about your Experience as a developer with SolidJS.\cb1 \
\cb3 Mental model simplicity is where Solid shines.\cb1 \
\cb3 If you understand JavaScript, you can understand Solid. There\'92s no special template syntax to learn, just JavaScript functions that return JSX.\cb1 \
\cb3 Components in Solid are simple factory functions that run once. They set up reactivity and return JSX \'97 then they\'92re done. This is fundamentally different from React\'92s constant re-rendering of components.\cb1 \
\cb3 For developers frustrated with the complexity of hooks in React, or the unexpected re-render behavior, Solid offers a refreshingly predictable development experience.\cb1 \
\cb3 Now let\'92s look at something that a lot of devs don\'92t consider.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs60 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb3 Bundle Size and Performance\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs40 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb3 Bundle size is another consideration. At roughly 7kb minified and gzipped, Solid is substantially smaller than React (around 40kb with React DOM).\cb1 \
\cb3 This matters for performance, especially on mobile devices.\cb1 \
\cb3 The small footprint means faster load times and better performance on lower-end devices.\cb1 \
\cb3 In 2025, as web applications continue to grow in complexity, keeping the framework overhead minimal becomes increasingly important.\cb1 \
\cb3 This size difference is not just about the initial download. The JavaScript execution time also impacts performance significantly. Smaller bundles generally mean less JavaScript to parse, compile, and execute, resulting in faster Time to Interactive metrics.\cb1 \
\cb3 In real-world applications, this translates to tangible benefits for users. A framework that loads 30kb less JavaScript can mean the difference between a user engaging with your content or bouncing from frustration, especially on slower connections or budget devices common in emerging markets.\cb1 \
\cb3 The Core Web Vitals metrics that Google uses to evaluate page experience are directly impacted by bundle size. Smaller bundles contribute to better Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) times and improved First Input Delay (FID) scores, which can positively affect SEO rankings and user experience.\cb1 \
\cb3 SolidJS achieves this efficiency without sacrificing developer ergonomics. Unlike some other lightweight alternatives that require verbose code or manual optimizations, Solid maintains a clean API while delivering exceptional performance.\cb1 \
\cb3 For enterprise applications where every kilobyte matters at scale, these savings multiply across millions of user sessions, potentially reducing CDN costs and bandwidth usage significantly over time.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
